This is how I would do loot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I would check out all of the people who play in my guild, and see who could use or would benefit the most from acquiring the item as well as looking at time spent on raids. If Player A had gone on just about as many raids as Player B, but player B had uberweapon from other big boss mob, I might suggest that Player A get the item if everyone agreed. <br>
<br>
The only problem with this system is that since a guild is big and not everyone might agree with this, as not everyone has the same set of values. (Ie some players no matter what just want more loot, and dont care that player A doesnt have a uberweapon, or even a decent weapon, and even go in for boobie weapons)<br>
